> Saucy, smothered, hearty, and delicious: This enchilada bake has everything you could
> possibly want. You'll start by wrapping tortillas around a filling of spiced ground
> pork and sautéed bell pepper, then coating the bundles with a healthy glug of zesty
> tomato sauce and a sprinkle of Mexican cheese. Bake until piping hot and bubbly,
> then top with lime crema and pico de gallo and dig into all that deliciousness.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 475 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce.

Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}. Quarter @Lime{1}. Core,
deseed, and dice @Green Bell Pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces.

== Pico de Gallo ==

In a #small bowl, combine @tomato{}, @scallions{}, a drizzle of oil, and juice from
1 lime wedge (2 wedges for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon} with lime juice to
taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan over medium-high
heat. Add bell pepper, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook until just softened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Add another drizzle of oil to pan. Add @Ground Pork{10%ounce}, half the
@Tex-Mex Paste{1}, half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until pork is browned and cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Place a small amount of filling on one half of each @Flour Tortillas{6}. Roll up
tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create enchiladas. Place seam sides
down in an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (9-by-13-inch baking dish for 4 servings)
or an #ovenproof pan.

In a #liquid measuring cup or #bowl, combine @water{½%cup} (¾ cup for 4 servings),
@Tomato Paste{1.5%ounce}, remaining Tex-Mex paste, and remaining Southwest Spice.

Pour sauce over enchiladas to thoroughly coat. Sprinkle with
@Mexican Cheese Blend{½%cup}.

Bake on top rack until sauce is bubbly and cheese has melted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Top enchiladas with lime crema and pico de gallo. Divide between plates and serve
with any remaining lime wedges on the side.